1
00:00:04,818 --> 00:00:06,986
<i>The serial murders happening recently…</i>

2
00:00:07,070 --> 00:00:08,988
<i>They are similar to the Shiramine case.</i>

3
00:00:09,072 --> 00:00:11,533
Could you please
tell me what happened back then?

4
00:00:11,616 --> 00:00:13,368
Stop making a fool out of me.

5
00:00:13,451 --> 00:00:15,286
Mizusawa Masumi, was it?

6
00:00:15,370 --> 00:00:16,996
<i>He is a bit of an eyesore, isn't he?</i>

7
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:19,916
MEJ will be shut down
by the end of this month.

8
00:00:25,463 --> 00:00:26,422
What?

9
00:00:26,506 --> 00:00:27,674
Shut down?

10
00:00:28,466 --> 00:00:29,717
Why so suddenly?

11
00:00:30,510 --> 00:00:32,303
Is there a reason for this?

12
00:00:32,929 --> 00:00:35,890
I haven't been told the details either.

13
00:00:36,891 --> 00:00:37,851
However,

14
00:00:37,934 --> 00:00:41,020
the MEJ was originally
an experimental operation,

15
00:00:41,521 --> 00:00:44,065
and the higher-ups said
they already have enough data

16
00:00:44,148 --> 00:00:47,777
to debate whether to officially
implement it.

17
00:00:48,695 --> 00:00:51,072
Even so, this is far too sudden.

18
00:00:51,698 --> 00:00:53,533
What are we supposed to do now?

19
00:00:57,453 --> 00:01:00,707
What you are all saying
is completely justified.

20
00:01:01,749 --> 00:01:04,544
I am truly sorry for my lack of skill.

21
00:01:05,044 --> 00:01:07,463
It's not your fault, Ms. Kiryu.

22
00:01:09,215 --> 00:01:12,177
Dr. Masumi,
you don't agree with this either, right?

23
00:01:14,304 --> 00:01:15,471
Dr. Masumi,

24
00:01:16,139 --> 00:01:17,098
I'm sorry.

25
00:01:20,810 --> 00:01:25,565
If only I had done a better job promoting
the significance of the MEJ…

26
00:01:25,648 --> 00:01:27,150
Ms. Kiryu,

27
00:01:28,151 --> 00:01:29,444
you are not to blame.

28
00:01:31,487 --> 00:01:32,739
It's my responsibility.

29
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:46,294
-Hello.
-Good work.

30
00:01:52,467 --> 00:01:53,301
Hello.

31
00:01:53,384 --> 00:01:54,219
Hello.

32
00:01:55,428 --> 00:01:57,347
Yukie Morishita, 23 years old.

33
00:01:57,430 --> 00:02:00,642
After she'd called her father
last night around 9 p.m.,

34
00:02:00,725 --> 00:02:02,352
she became unreachable.

35
00:02:02,852 --> 00:02:05,063
A passerby discovered the body
this morning.

36
00:02:05,146 --> 00:02:07,690
Another strangulation of a young woman…

37
00:02:08,191 --> 00:02:10,235
It has finally happened
in our jurisdiction too.

38
00:02:10,318 --> 00:02:11,819
This makes six victims already.

39
00:02:15,114 --> 00:02:16,866
It really is similar.

40
00:02:16,950 --> 00:02:17,951
What?

41
00:02:19,619 --> 00:02:21,996
Well, I'll contact the MEJ.

42
00:02:22,705 --> 00:02:25,792
Oh, they're gone now, right? Sorry.

43
00:02:34,050 --> 00:02:36,135
I'll leave it to you.

44
00:02:39,514 --> 00:02:41,099
Ms. Kiryu, here.

45
00:02:41,182 --> 00:02:42,350
Please review this.

46
00:02:43,559 --> 00:02:44,727
Oh, okay.

47
00:02:46,980 --> 00:02:50,149
Are you still thinking about the MEJ?

48
00:02:51,317 --> 00:02:52,777
Oh, yes.

49
00:02:54,195 --> 00:02:56,406
It's not your fault.

50
00:02:57,073 --> 00:03:01,619
In the first place, Japan isn't ready
for the MEJ system itself.

51
00:03:03,913 --> 00:03:06,874
All the staff members
managed to find new workplaces, right?

52
00:03:08,793 --> 00:03:11,754
I heard that you found them their jobs.

53
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:16,426
I somehow managed to find positions
for all the young doctors.

54
00:03:17,093 --> 00:03:19,470
Then you've got nothing to worry about.

55
00:03:28,479 --> 00:03:32,316
Your mother
was trying to protect someone else,

56
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:34,152
and got into an accident.

57
00:03:38,865 --> 00:03:40,908
That is not something just anyone can do.

58
00:03:41,909 --> 00:03:43,453
She was an incredible person.

59
00:03:45,121 --> 00:03:46,789
How do you know?

60
00:03:48,124 --> 00:03:50,209
I know by listening to their voices.

61
00:03:50,293 --> 00:03:53,212
But people can't talk once they're dead.

62
00:03:53,713 --> 00:03:54,881
That's true.

63
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,883
But…

64
00:03:58,051 --> 00:03:59,844
I can listen to them.

65
00:04:12,106 --> 00:04:13,107
Come in.

66
00:04:14,108 --> 00:04:15,276
Excuse me.

67
00:04:18,446 --> 00:04:19,614
Masumi?

68
00:04:23,826 --> 00:04:25,119
The other day,

69
00:04:25,620 --> 00:04:29,374
I went to meet Shinichi Serizawa
at the detention center.

70
00:04:31,334 --> 00:04:36,756
I asked him if he would tell me
what happened back then once more,

71
00:04:37,965 --> 00:04:39,550
but he refused.

72
00:04:41,010 --> 00:04:42,136
I see.

73
00:04:43,638 --> 00:04:44,639
And,

74
00:04:45,723 --> 00:04:51,187
the MEJ was suddenly shut down.

75
00:04:53,856 --> 00:04:57,110
On the surface,
it was a notice from the MHLW,

76
00:04:57,735 --> 00:04:58,861
but maybe,

77
00:04:59,862 --> 00:05:02,824
it's a warning from the prosecution

78
00:05:03,449 --> 00:05:06,911
not to dig any deeper
into the Shiramine case.

79
00:05:09,455 --> 00:05:11,707
It's one thing if it's just me,

80
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:16,504
but taking away the workplace
of young forensic pathologists

81
00:05:18,297 --> 00:05:20,633
is something I can't ever accept.

82
00:05:21,634 --> 00:05:25,638
I believe we cannot back down now,
for the sake of Serizawa,

83
00:05:26,431 --> 00:05:28,474
who maintains his innocence.

84
00:05:31,102 --> 00:05:32,854
I will ask you once more.

85
00:05:34,647 --> 00:05:36,190
What on earth

86
00:05:36,941 --> 00:05:38,401
happened back then?

87
00:05:42,947 --> 00:05:44,031
Professor,

88
00:05:44,907 --> 00:05:46,951
please tell me the truth!

89
00:05:52,331 --> 00:05:57,128
There are people
who have been suffering for 15 years.

90
00:05:57,211 --> 00:06:00,423
Besides, we cannot allow any more victims.

91
00:06:01,674 --> 00:06:05,553
What is it that you are trying
to protect, Professor?

92
00:06:08,514 --> 00:06:11,100
Listening to the final voices
of the deceased…

93
00:06:11,601 --> 00:06:15,897
The person who taught me
how to face someone's loved one

94
00:06:16,981 --> 00:06:18,691
was you, Professor.

95
00:06:27,825 --> 00:06:28,993
I…

96
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:34,999
will not give up again.

97
00:06:49,430 --> 00:06:52,558
I believe in you, Professor.

98
00:07:21,212 --> 00:07:22,171
Yukie?

99
00:07:26,092 --> 00:07:26,926
Yukie?

100
00:07:29,136 --> 00:07:31,013
Why? Why?!

101
00:07:31,097 --> 00:07:32,640
Yukie!

102
00:07:34,809 --> 00:07:36,352
Yukie!

103
00:07:37,937 --> 00:07:39,021
Why…

104
00:07:42,024 --> 00:07:43,192
Yukie…

105
00:07:49,365 --> 00:07:50,575
Mr. Morishita.

106
00:07:52,660 --> 00:07:55,788
We will now have to perform

107
00:07:56,455 --> 00:07:59,458
a judicial autopsy on Yukie's body.

108
00:08:00,501 --> 00:08:01,460
Autopsy?

109
00:08:02,878 --> 00:08:05,089
It is to investigate
Yukie's cause of death

110
00:08:05,172 --> 00:08:07,800
and find traces
that might lead to the perpetrator.

111
00:08:07,883 --> 00:08:09,260
Don't!

112
00:08:11,971 --> 00:08:15,016
Yukie has already gone through
something so terrible.

113
00:08:18,311 --> 00:08:21,147
Please don't hurt my daughter any more.

114
00:08:21,814 --> 00:08:23,691
I understand how you feel.

115
00:08:24,567 --> 00:08:25,526
However,

116
00:08:27,278 --> 00:08:32,450
a judicial autopsy cannot be stopped
by the wishes of the bereaved family.

117
00:08:35,119 --> 00:08:36,537
I am truly sorry.

118
00:08:47,173 --> 00:08:48,841
<i>Moving on to the next story,</i>

119
00:08:48,924 --> 00:08:53,596
<i>this morning, the body of a young woman</i>
<i>was discovered on a street in Tokyo.</i>

120
00:08:53,679 --> 00:08:55,681
<i>According to investigative sources,</i>

121
00:08:55,765 --> 00:08:58,434
<i>authorities are proceeding</i>
<i>under the belief</i>

122
00:08:58,517 --> 00:09:00,895
<i>that this is connected</i>
<i>to the serial murders.</i>

123
00:09:00,978 --> 00:09:04,857
<i>As of now, no definitive eyewitness</i>
<i>information has been obtained…</i>

124
00:09:09,195 --> 00:09:10,112
Hello!

125
00:09:10,821 --> 00:09:15,117
No eyewitnesses and not a trace
that might lead to the killer.

126
00:09:15,201 --> 00:09:17,536
-You can't enter here!
-Please let me through.

127
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:19,622
No unauthorized personnel may enter.

128
00:09:20,956 --> 00:09:22,041
Please.

129
00:09:22,124 --> 00:09:24,251
-The investigation is--
-Isn't that Dr. Masumi?

130
00:09:24,335 --> 00:09:25,503
Why is he here?

131
00:09:25,586 --> 00:09:27,338
Let me explain again.

132
00:09:27,421 --> 00:09:28,589
Doctor.

133
00:09:28,673 --> 00:09:29,840
What are you doing?

134
00:09:29,924 --> 00:09:31,676
Ms. Dojima, I'm glad you're here.

135
00:09:32,259 --> 00:09:34,845
Could you please
let me investigate the case as well?

136
00:09:35,471 --> 00:09:36,681
I can't do that.

137
00:09:37,181 --> 00:09:38,099
What?

138
00:09:38,182 --> 00:09:41,977
No one except those involved
in the investigation can enter here.

139
00:09:42,061 --> 00:09:44,230
You aren't involved anymore, right?

140
00:09:44,313 --> 00:09:47,191
Could you at least let me see the body?

141
00:09:47,274 --> 00:09:50,528
The body is already
on its way to the autopsy.

142
00:09:51,153 --> 00:09:52,571
Please leave.

143
00:09:53,155 --> 00:09:57,034
This serial murder case might be connected
to an incident from the past!

144
00:09:57,118 --> 00:10:00,746
There's no way that's true!
Don't make up things to try to get in.

145
00:10:00,830 --> 00:10:01,831
Right?

146
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:06,544
Tell me more.

147
00:10:23,978 --> 00:10:27,022
Are you Yukie Morishita's father?

148
00:10:28,649 --> 00:10:29,525
Yes.

149
00:10:30,151 --> 00:10:33,529
My name is Kyoko Kujo. I'm a pathologist.

150
00:10:34,530 --> 00:10:36,907
I will be performing
the autopsy on your daughter.

151
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,368
Doctor…

152
00:10:40,911 --> 00:10:44,290
Do you really have to do the autopsy?

153
00:10:46,792 --> 00:10:51,088
I can't bear for my daughter's body
to be hurt any more than it has.

154
00:10:52,715 --> 00:10:55,551
I really do understand how you feel.

155
00:10:57,887 --> 00:10:59,221
After work…

156
00:11:00,973 --> 00:11:03,058
I should have just taken her home.

157
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:06,687
Because of me, Yukie…

158
00:11:06,771 --> 00:11:08,689
It is not your fault.

159
00:11:09,356 --> 00:11:12,693
The one at fault is the criminal
who took your daughter's life.

160
00:11:14,862 --> 00:11:17,114
To get justice for your daughter,

161
00:11:17,865 --> 00:11:20,701
please allow me to investigate this.

162
00:11:28,959 --> 00:11:32,421
Please take care of my daughter.

163
00:11:51,649 --> 00:11:52,775
SHIRAMINE SERIAL FEMICIDE CASE

164
00:11:52,858 --> 00:11:54,109
I knew it.

165
00:11:54,735 --> 00:11:57,321
This is about
the Shiramine case, isn't it?

166
00:11:58,113 --> 00:11:59,740
-Yes.
-Huh?

167
00:11:59,823 --> 00:12:02,076
What is the Shiramine case?

168
00:12:02,159 --> 00:12:03,702
It was a series of murders

169
00:12:04,245 --> 00:12:08,290
that took place in West Tokyo,
in Shiramine, 15 years ago.

170
00:12:09,291 --> 00:12:12,461
<i>The three victims</i>
<i>were all females in their twenties,</i>

171
00:12:12,545 --> 00:12:15,130
<i>and the cause of death</i>
<i>was always strangulation</i>

172
00:12:15,214 --> 00:12:17,883
<i>by something like a belt.</i>

173
00:12:18,467 --> 00:12:19,885
<i>Shinichi Serizawa,</i>

174
00:12:19,969 --> 00:12:23,639
<i>who worked at the same place</i>
<i>as one of the victims, was arrested.</i>

175
00:12:23,722 --> 00:12:25,266
<i>He was found guilty</i>

176
00:12:25,349 --> 00:12:28,394
<i>and his death penalty</i>
<i>was finalized because of DNA evidence</i>

177
00:12:28,477 --> 00:12:31,605
<i>and lack of an alibi</i>
<i>at the estimated time of death.</i>

178
00:12:32,856 --> 00:12:35,401
Strangling young women…

179
00:12:35,484 --> 00:12:38,612
It's just like the serial killings
happening right now.

180
00:12:39,488 --> 00:12:41,156
I was considering that maybe

181
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:44,743
this is the work of a copycat criminal
imitating the Shiramine case.

182
00:12:44,827 --> 00:12:45,786
A copycat?

183
00:12:47,705 --> 00:12:48,831
I…

184
00:12:49,623 --> 00:12:51,125
don't think so.

185
00:12:52,793 --> 00:12:54,587
I don't suspect a copycat.

186
00:12:55,254 --> 00:12:57,631
I suspect the possibility
of a repeat offense.

187
00:12:57,715 --> 00:12:59,008
A repeat offense?

188
00:12:59,633 --> 00:13:00,593
On what grounds?

189
00:13:00,676 --> 00:13:03,971
But you just said the culprit
was already caught, didn't you?

190
00:13:04,054 --> 00:13:08,809
The forensic examiner
in charge of the Shiramine case

191
00:13:09,476 --> 00:13:12,187
was my mentor, Professor Kujo.

192
00:13:12,771 --> 00:13:17,359
<i>I also participated in the autopsy</i>
<i>as an assistant.</i>

193
00:13:18,819 --> 00:13:21,572
However, those forensic findings

194
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:25,826
differed from the facts.

195
00:13:26,869 --> 00:13:28,329
What do you mean?

196
00:13:28,412 --> 00:13:30,080
During the autopsy,

197
00:13:30,164 --> 00:13:34,877
skin fragments believed to belong
to the killer were found on the body,

198
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:39,632
but there wasn't a sufficient amount
to perform a DNA test.

199
00:13:40,758 --> 00:13:41,967
And yet,

200
00:13:42,843 --> 00:13:45,971
the forensic report
he submitted to the prosecution

201
00:13:46,055 --> 00:13:50,142
<i>stated that it matched</i>
<i>Serizawa's DNA profile.</i>

202
00:13:50,225 --> 00:13:53,812
So that doctor
fabricated the forensic results

203
00:13:54,396 --> 00:13:58,609
just to frame
Shinichi Serizawa as the culprit?

204
00:13:59,276 --> 00:14:00,319
Most likely.

205
00:14:06,533 --> 00:14:08,118
Professor Kujo

206
00:14:09,036 --> 00:14:13,165
is the person who performed
the autopsy on my mother

207
00:14:13,791 --> 00:14:16,210
after she died in an accident
when I was a child.

208
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:23,550
When I was frightened of my mother's body

209
00:14:24,218 --> 00:14:27,221
<i>and was unable to face her death,</i>

210
00:14:29,181 --> 00:14:31,100
<i>he said it wasn't just a dead body.</i>

211
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:36,689
He explained to me she was
a person who had loved,

212
00:14:37,731 --> 00:14:39,608
and was loved by others.

213
00:14:41,777 --> 00:14:43,362
Those words

214
00:14:44,238 --> 00:14:47,491
really saved me.

215
00:14:50,869 --> 00:14:52,246
For Professor Kujo

216
00:14:53,789 --> 00:14:56,291
to fabricate forensic results…

217
00:14:57,710 --> 00:15:00,462
They must have put
an immense amount of pressure on him.

218
00:15:04,466 --> 00:15:06,051
At the time,

219
00:15:06,927 --> 00:15:11,015
I realized the fabrication
and tried to blow the whistle on him,

220
00:15:11,098 --> 00:15:12,266
but…

221
00:15:13,017 --> 00:15:15,436
I was kicked out of the lab

222
00:15:16,270 --> 00:15:19,732
and couldn't gather enough evidence.

223
00:15:21,191 --> 00:15:25,654
I knew that the autopsy I was involved in
had created a wrongful conviction.

224
00:15:26,989 --> 00:15:31,118
I just couldn't accept that fact.

225
00:15:32,745 --> 00:15:34,955
I fled Japan.

226
00:15:42,921 --> 00:15:44,882
If Serizawa is innocent,

227
00:15:46,842 --> 00:15:49,511
then the real culprit is still out there.

228
00:15:49,595 --> 00:15:51,513
Does that mean that same killer

229
00:15:52,514 --> 00:15:57,269
is now murdering people again?

230
00:15:57,352 --> 00:15:59,104
It's a possibility.

231
00:15:59,188 --> 00:16:00,856
But it has been 15 years.

232
00:16:00,939 --> 00:16:02,524
Why would they start again now?

233
00:16:03,901 --> 00:16:04,902
I don't know.

234
00:16:05,486 --> 00:16:07,446
-You're overthinking this.
-No…

235
00:16:08,405 --> 00:16:10,449
It might actually make sense.

236
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:11,867
What?

237
00:16:12,367 --> 00:16:15,079
At the time, the investigation
was getting desperate

238
00:16:15,162 --> 00:16:17,831
because they couldn't identify a suspect.

239
00:16:17,915 --> 00:16:19,917
Then, eyewitness information on Serizawa

240
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,087
surfaced at a suspiciously
convenient time.

241
00:16:24,129 --> 00:16:26,507
Meaning they fabricated
the eyewitness testimony?

242
00:16:26,590 --> 00:16:28,884
I thought it was just a rumor.

243
00:16:28,967 --> 00:16:31,053
But if it's true…

244
00:16:33,055 --> 00:16:34,681
then the Shiramine case

245
00:16:35,265 --> 00:16:39,603
is something the prosecution
would definitely want to keep buried.

246
00:16:39,686 --> 00:16:45,400
That's why when the prosecution found out
I met with Professor Kujo and Serizawa,

247
00:16:45,484 --> 00:16:50,781
they pressured the Ministry
to force the closure of the MEJ.

248
00:16:50,864 --> 00:16:53,909
All to cover up their past blunder.

249
00:16:53,992 --> 00:16:57,204
Ms. Dojima, it's better
if you don't dig any deeper into this.

250
00:16:57,287 --> 00:16:59,665
What do you plan to do now, Dr. Masumi?

251
00:16:59,748 --> 00:17:00,916
I…

252
00:17:03,210 --> 00:17:06,421
I want to uncover the truth
behind the Shiramine case

253
00:17:06,505 --> 00:17:08,507
and clear Serizawa's name.

254
00:17:08,590 --> 00:17:09,675
To do that,

255
00:17:09,758 --> 00:17:14,763
I intend to find the real culprit
of the current serial killings.

256
00:17:16,181 --> 00:17:17,891
What do you mean by that?

257
00:17:19,351 --> 00:17:20,811
Supervisor.

258
00:17:20,894 --> 00:17:22,271
What brings you here?

259
00:17:22,354 --> 00:17:25,440
I just came to pack up my things
before our move-out.

260
00:17:27,234 --> 00:17:29,903
I'm sorry. We were using this room
without permission.

261
00:17:29,987 --> 00:17:30,988
Never mind that.

262
00:17:31,071 --> 00:17:33,866
What do you mean by a wrongful conviction?

263
00:17:45,335 --> 00:17:47,087
Sorry, I'm late.

264
00:17:48,005 --> 00:17:49,923
Were you busy today?

265
00:17:50,007 --> 00:17:50,924
Yes.

266
00:17:51,008 --> 00:17:54,928
After the autopsy, I had to take Haruto
to his cram school.

267
00:18:00,726 --> 00:18:01,810
Kyoko.

268
00:18:04,188 --> 00:18:05,397
I have a favor to ask.

269
00:18:09,109 --> 00:18:13,697
At the very bottom of my desk drawer,

270
00:18:14,489 --> 00:18:17,201
there is an old envelope.

271
00:18:18,118 --> 00:18:19,369
Bring it to me.

272
00:18:20,412 --> 00:18:21,496
An envelope?

273
00:18:23,165 --> 00:18:27,169
It's the forensic data
from the Shiramine case.

274
00:18:30,964 --> 00:18:32,674
What are you going to do with it?

275
00:18:35,177 --> 00:18:37,054
I'm going to give it to Masumi.

276
00:18:40,474 --> 00:18:42,601
Did Masumi put you up to this?

277
00:18:44,144 --> 00:18:45,187
No.

278
00:18:45,938 --> 00:18:47,439
This is my own choice.

279
00:18:48,774 --> 00:18:49,942
Why?

280
00:18:53,070 --> 00:18:54,863
It's always about Masumi with you.

281
00:18:56,740 --> 00:18:58,533
That's not true.

282
00:18:59,201 --> 00:19:01,620
Think about Haruto.

283
00:19:01,703 --> 00:19:03,580
This is a critical time.

284
00:19:03,664 --> 00:19:07,209
And besides,
that case is already over, isn't it?

285
00:19:08,877 --> 00:19:11,797
We just concluded that it was.

286
00:19:16,927 --> 00:19:18,553
I can't just die

287
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:22,683
leaving things like this.

288
00:19:37,531 --> 00:19:39,199
KYOKO KUJO

289
00:19:40,325 --> 00:19:41,285
Hello?

290
00:19:42,703 --> 00:19:43,704
<i>Masumi?</i>

291
00:19:43,787 --> 00:19:46,081
Kyoko. What's wrong?

292
00:19:46,957 --> 00:19:49,042
Sorry to call out of the blue.

293
00:19:49,626 --> 00:19:51,044
Did something happen?

294
00:19:51,128 --> 00:19:53,338
My father has a message for you.

295
00:19:54,047 --> 00:19:56,925
It seems he has some data
he wants to hand over to you.

296
00:20:00,012 --> 00:20:03,015
<i>Can you come pick them up</i>
<i>when you have time?</i>

297
00:20:03,098 --> 00:20:04,433
I'll come tomorrow.

298
00:20:05,309 --> 00:20:08,103
Tell the professor I'll come tomorrow.

299
00:20:10,272 --> 00:20:11,273
All right.

300
00:20:13,025 --> 00:20:15,360
Thanks for calling.

301
00:20:27,914 --> 00:20:30,208
SHIRAMINE SERIAL FEMICIDE CASE

302
00:20:35,672 --> 00:20:37,591
MINISTRY OF HEALTH, LABOR AND WELFARE

303
00:20:40,719 --> 00:20:45,557
Are you trying to clear
a wrongful conviction all by yourself?

304
00:20:45,640 --> 00:20:48,852
I believe that's also why the MEJ

305
00:20:50,604 --> 00:20:52,230
was suddenly shut down.

306
00:20:54,733 --> 00:20:56,860
Kiryu, do you have a minute?

307
00:20:57,611 --> 00:20:58,528
Coming.

308
00:21:01,365 --> 00:21:02,407
What is it?

309
00:21:02,491 --> 00:21:05,410
Since you've finally returned
to our department,

310
00:21:05,494 --> 00:21:07,454
I would like to ask you to handle this.

311
00:21:07,537 --> 00:21:09,581
SUPPORT FOR YOUNG PEOPLE
EXPERIENCING FINANCIAL HARDSHIP

312
00:21:09,664 --> 00:21:10,749
What?

313
00:21:10,832 --> 00:21:11,792
Isn't this…

314
00:21:11,875 --> 00:21:15,379
It's the youth poverty support project
that you submitted before.

315
00:21:15,962 --> 00:21:19,633
But I thought someone else
was put in charge of this.

316
00:21:19,716 --> 00:21:22,677
At the time, I wanted you
to focus entirely on the MEJ,

317
00:21:22,761 --> 00:21:24,930
but you are the right fit
for this after all.

318
00:21:28,433 --> 00:21:29,351
Thank you.

319
00:21:30,018 --> 00:21:30,936
Good luck.

320
00:21:31,019 --> 00:21:32,479
I'm expecting great things.

321
00:21:40,070 --> 00:21:41,613
That's great.

322
00:21:41,696 --> 00:21:44,533
It's the project
you've wanted to handle for ages.

323
00:21:55,210 --> 00:21:58,255
So, how is everyone's new workplace?

324
00:21:58,338 --> 00:21:59,673
Are you doing well?

325
00:21:59,756 --> 00:22:03,427
We have a full staff,
and it's actually not bad.

326
00:22:04,511 --> 00:22:07,681
To be honest, I've been able
to spend more time with my kid.

327
00:22:08,598 --> 00:22:11,017
They let me leave right on time every day.

328
00:22:11,101 --> 00:22:12,102
Me too.

329
00:22:12,602 --> 00:22:14,688
When they suddenly told us
we were closing,

330
00:22:14,771 --> 00:22:16,565
I wondered what would happen, but…

331
00:22:17,482 --> 00:22:21,736
It must have been really tough for
Ms. Kiryu to find new jobs for all of us.

332
00:22:21,820 --> 00:22:25,657
But don't you sort of miss
the vibe at the MEJ?

333
00:22:25,740 --> 00:22:28,201
I know, the adrenaline rush
from being so busy.

334
00:22:28,285 --> 00:22:32,247
We even pulled all-nighters,
so at the time I just wanted a break,

335
00:22:32,873 --> 00:22:35,208
but I was gradually starting to enjoy it.

336
00:22:36,293 --> 00:22:39,129
We were really starting
to come together as a team…

337
00:22:41,047 --> 00:22:44,634
But still, don't you think it's weird
for it to close down so abruptly?

338
00:22:44,718 --> 00:22:46,136
It is absolutely weird.

339
00:22:46,803 --> 00:22:51,224
Well, the Ministry decided it,
so I guess there's nothing we can do.

340
00:22:51,308 --> 00:22:52,142
Even so,

341
00:22:52,225 --> 00:22:54,811
shutting it down after a few months
is strange for sure.

342
00:22:56,313 --> 00:22:59,816
There must be some other reason behind it.

343
00:23:01,234 --> 00:23:02,319
Some other reason?

344
00:23:17,876 --> 00:23:18,793
Excuse me.

345
00:23:36,353 --> 00:23:37,479
Masumi.

346
00:23:43,068 --> 00:23:44,444
Where is Professor Kujo?

347
00:23:46,780 --> 00:23:48,740
His condition deteriorated overnight.

348
00:23:52,494 --> 00:23:53,912
He passed away this morning.

349
00:23:57,707 --> 00:24:00,335
The documents he wanted to give you…

350
00:24:01,002 --> 00:24:03,964
I can't find where they are anymore.

351
00:24:05,548 --> 00:24:06,549
What?

352
00:24:07,175 --> 00:24:10,303
I have to go now to handle the procedures.

353
00:24:15,892 --> 00:24:16,893
Masumi.

354
00:24:21,481 --> 00:24:24,067
Please don't make my father
suffer any more than this.

355
00:24:56,850 --> 00:24:57,934
<i>Professor,</i>

356
00:24:58,018 --> 00:25:00,312
please tell me the truth!

357
00:25:12,657 --> 00:25:14,909
<i>A group supporting Shinichi Serizawa,</i>

358
00:25:14,993 --> 00:25:18,788
<i>who received the death sentence</i>
<i>for the murder of three women</i>

359
00:25:18,872 --> 00:25:21,916
<i>which happened in Shiramine 15 years ago,</i>

360
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,836
<i>has started a petition drive,</i>
<i>claiming his innocence.</i>

361
00:25:24,919 --> 00:25:27,297
<i>My brother is no murderer!</i>

362
00:25:28,298 --> 00:25:31,217
<i>Please lend us your support</i>
<i>so we can get a retrial!</i>

363
00:25:32,218 --> 00:25:37,724
<i>We are only demanding that the trial</i>
<i>be conducted fairly, a just trial.</i>

364
00:25:37,807 --> 00:25:40,894
Wow, she has really kept at it
for 15 years.

365
00:25:40,977 --> 00:25:43,772
It's nearly impossible
to get a case reopened.

366
00:25:45,523 --> 00:25:46,691
Speaking of which,

367
00:25:47,317 --> 00:25:50,570
I heard that the forensic pathologist,
Masahito Kujo, passed away.

368
00:25:51,571 --> 00:25:56,409
Then we don't have to worry about him
saying anything unnecessary anymore.

369
00:25:56,493 --> 00:25:57,619
However,

370
00:25:57,702 --> 00:26:01,831
the family might still have the original
copies of the autopsy documents.

371
00:26:03,625 --> 00:26:05,210
Just to be safe,

372
00:26:06,044 --> 00:26:08,254
make sure to stamp out
even the smallest spark.

373
00:26:10,131 --> 00:26:11,341
Understood.

374
00:26:15,804 --> 00:26:18,723
Are you making progress
in packing up the MEJ office?

375
00:26:18,807 --> 00:26:22,185
I'm sorry. There are return procedures
for the testing equipment,

376
00:26:22,268 --> 00:26:24,270
so could you give me a little more time?

377
00:26:24,354 --> 00:26:25,355
All right.

378
00:26:25,438 --> 00:26:26,773
I'll leave the rest to you.

379
00:26:26,856 --> 00:26:28,316
Please hurry, though.

380
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:29,484
Understood.

381
00:26:32,195 --> 00:26:35,740
Regarding the autopsy records
Professor Kujo owned,

382
00:26:35,824 --> 00:26:38,410
I wasn't able to receive them.

383
00:26:38,493 --> 00:26:39,369
I see.

384
00:26:39,452 --> 00:26:40,578
However,

385
00:26:41,121 --> 00:26:45,667
while less definitive than that data,
there is one other lead.

386
00:26:47,085 --> 00:26:51,798
The documents the prosecution
submitted during the trial back then

387
00:26:51,881 --> 00:26:56,302
include crime scene photos and other
materials that haven't been made public.

388
00:26:57,429 --> 00:27:00,223
The family requesting the retrial

389
00:27:00,306 --> 00:27:03,101
might have obtained them
through their lawyer.

390
00:27:03,852 --> 00:27:04,894
Yes.

391
00:27:04,978 --> 00:27:07,772
Shinichi Serizawa is innocent!

392
00:27:07,856 --> 00:27:10,275
Let's help save him!

393
00:27:10,859 --> 00:27:13,445
Shinichi Serizawa is innocent!

394
00:27:13,528 --> 00:27:15,155
Please.

395
00:27:15,238 --> 00:27:16,948
Please.

396
00:27:17,031 --> 00:27:19,284
I want to prove my brother's innocence.

397
00:27:19,367 --> 00:27:20,994
Please help.

398
00:27:23,580 --> 00:27:24,998
Thank you very much.

399
00:27:47,645 --> 00:27:51,024
I apologize for dropping in on you
so suddenly.

400
00:27:52,692 --> 00:27:56,446
I had a few things
I wanted to say to you as well.

401
00:27:59,741 --> 00:28:01,242
For the past 15 years,

402
00:28:02,076 --> 00:28:06,998
I haven't forgotten your name
or Masahito Kujo's name even once.

403
00:28:08,917 --> 00:28:11,044
Because of your autopsy report,

404
00:28:11,669 --> 00:28:15,548
my brother was sentenced to death
for murders he didn't commit.

405
00:28:18,092 --> 00:28:19,052
How dare you

406
00:28:20,303 --> 00:28:22,055
show your face here after that?

407
00:28:29,103 --> 00:28:31,105
I am truly sorry for what happened.

408
00:28:33,816 --> 00:28:35,944
Do you think an apology makes it right?

409
00:28:37,070 --> 00:28:38,071
It was an irreparable--

410
00:28:38,154 --> 00:28:40,406
Shinichi's life has been changed forever.

411
00:28:41,616 --> 00:28:42,575
Our parents

412
00:28:43,868 --> 00:28:48,790
passed away while desperately
proclaiming Shinichi's innocence.

413
00:28:50,124 --> 00:28:52,001
They felt nothing but regret.

414
00:28:55,129 --> 00:28:57,799
Because of your careless autopsy,

415
00:28:59,759 --> 00:29:02,512
our family's lives were completely ruined.

416
00:29:06,558 --> 00:29:08,184
What on earth

417
00:29:09,435 --> 00:29:11,229
do you want after all this time?

418
00:29:17,527 --> 00:29:19,863
The current serial murder case

419
00:29:21,281 --> 00:29:24,826
involving the deaths of six women

420
00:29:25,827 --> 00:29:29,873
might be the work of the real culprit
from the Shiramine incident.

421
00:29:32,417 --> 00:29:34,919
There's a possibility
that the real killer,

422
00:29:35,003 --> 00:29:36,588
who was never caught,

423
00:29:37,505 --> 00:29:40,049
is committing murders again right now.

424
00:29:41,050 --> 00:29:43,094
If we find the real culprit,

425
00:29:43,177 --> 00:29:46,014
we can prove Shinichi's innocence.

426
00:29:47,223 --> 00:29:49,934
To clear Shinichi's name
from this wrongful conviction,

427
00:29:50,018 --> 00:29:52,604
won't you let me look into it once more?

428
00:29:52,687 --> 00:29:54,856
Why are you asking me?

429
00:29:55,648 --> 00:29:58,526
You should just ask the person
who performed the autopsy.

430
00:30:03,865 --> 00:30:06,618
He passed away the other day.

431
00:30:09,078 --> 00:30:12,290
If you have the trial documents
from back then,

432
00:30:12,373 --> 00:30:14,292
would you please show them to me?

433
00:30:14,375 --> 00:30:16,002
Please, I beg you.

434
00:30:20,757 --> 00:30:21,966
Do you think

435
00:30:23,134 --> 00:30:26,012
I could trust anything you say?

436
00:30:33,645 --> 00:30:36,898
Never show your face in front of me again.

437
00:30:37,690 --> 00:30:38,691
Wait!

438
00:30:39,275 --> 00:30:41,527
I want to clear Shinichi's name!

439
00:30:41,611 --> 00:30:43,988
Don't speak my brother's name so casually!

440
00:30:50,453 --> 00:30:53,706
For 15 years,
there hasn't been a single day

441
00:30:53,790 --> 00:30:58,920
I haven't thought about
the Shiramine case either.

442
00:31:05,885 --> 00:31:09,889
Please let me uncover the truth!

443
00:31:34,038 --> 00:31:35,248
Mama!

444
00:31:47,719 --> 00:31:49,512
Thank you very much.

445
00:31:51,723 --> 00:31:53,808
You're Kyoko Kujo, correct?

446
00:31:55,685 --> 00:31:58,938
I'm Ota from the Tokyo District
Public Prosecutors Office.

447
00:32:00,231 --> 00:32:01,274
Here.

448
00:32:04,819 --> 00:32:08,281
My condolences regarding your father.

449
00:32:10,491 --> 00:32:12,744
Is this about the Shiramine case?

450
00:32:14,162 --> 00:32:16,039
Thank you for catching on so quickly.

451
00:32:16,706 --> 00:32:20,626
Could you hand over the autopsy documents
your father kept?

452
00:32:23,755 --> 00:32:25,256
There are no such documents.

453
00:32:27,508 --> 00:32:28,593
Excuse me.

454
00:32:30,219 --> 00:32:31,095
Haruto!

455
00:32:31,179 --> 00:32:32,305
Let's go.

456
00:32:35,808 --> 00:32:36,726
Did you have fun?

457
00:32:41,481 --> 00:32:43,983
<i>The investigation is progressing.</i>

458
00:32:44,484 --> 00:32:45,777
<i>Now, for the next story.</i>

459
00:32:46,277 --> 00:32:49,072
<i>Regarding a series of murders</i>
<i>targeting young women</i>

460
00:32:49,155 --> 00:32:51,324
<i>which are believed to be connected,</i>

461
00:32:51,407 --> 00:32:53,826
<i>we have interviewed</i>
<i>a family member of one victim.</i>

462
00:32:54,410 --> 00:32:57,497
<i>My wife died young.</i>

463
00:32:57,580 --> 00:32:58,790
YUKIE MORISHITA'S FATHER

464
00:32:58,873 --> 00:33:01,751
<i>I raised my daughter trying to make up</i>
<i>for her mother's absence.</i>

465
00:33:01,834 --> 00:33:03,127
<i>Why?</i>

466
00:33:03,211 --> 00:33:06,464
<i>Why did this have to happen</i>
<i>to my daughter?</i>

467
00:33:06,547 --> 00:33:09,050
<i>She didn't do anything wrong.</i>

468
00:33:09,842 --> 00:33:11,677
<i>I want Yukie back!</i>

469
00:33:12,678 --> 00:33:16,140
<i>Five other victims are believed</i>
<i>to be connected to this case.</i>

470
00:33:16,224 --> 00:33:19,060
<i>But there have currently</i>
<i>not been any arrests,</i>

471
00:33:19,143 --> 00:33:21,104
<i>and the investigators are at a loss.</i>

472
00:33:21,187 --> 00:33:23,147
<i>There's a possibility</i>
<i>that the real killer,</i>

473
00:33:23,231 --> 00:33:25,858
<i>who was never caught,</i>
<i>is committing murders again right now.</i>

474
00:33:25,942 --> 00:33:29,570
<i>Please let me uncover the truth!</i>

475
00:33:41,082 --> 00:33:46,879
I went to see Akiko,
Serizawa's older sister, but…

476
00:33:48,464 --> 00:33:50,341
she said she can't trust me

477
00:33:51,259 --> 00:33:53,052
and refused.

478
00:33:54,595 --> 00:33:55,596
I see.

479
00:33:56,180 --> 00:33:58,141
Professor Kujo and I…

480
00:33:59,976 --> 00:34:03,020
This is what we've done.

481
00:34:17,118 --> 00:34:18,161
What's this?

482
00:34:18,870 --> 00:34:22,415
Investigative materials
on the current serial murder case.

483
00:34:22,957 --> 00:34:25,042
I thought it might be of some reference.

484
00:34:26,294 --> 00:34:27,420
Are you sure?

485
00:34:27,503 --> 00:34:29,839
If I get caught, my head will roll.

486
00:34:30,882 --> 00:34:32,049
But with this,

487
00:34:32,967 --> 00:34:36,637
you might be able to find
the real killer, Dr. Masumi.

488
00:34:43,811 --> 00:34:45,313
Thank you very much.

489
00:34:48,524 --> 00:34:50,735
Six people have already been killed.

490
00:34:51,235 --> 00:34:53,863
If you include the Shiramine case,
it's nine people.

491
00:34:54,363 --> 00:34:55,656
Yukie!

492
00:34:56,240 --> 00:34:57,825
Yukie!

493
00:35:01,037 --> 00:35:04,165
I want to catch the culprit
no matter what.

494
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:08,002
I will do whatever I can for that.

495
00:35:09,253 --> 00:35:10,379
I will also

496
00:35:11,214 --> 00:35:12,840
give everything I have.

497
00:35:31,317 --> 00:35:32,693
SIXTH CASE INVESTIGATION PHOTOS

498
00:35:34,153 --> 00:35:36,656
MURDER OF A FEMALE
OFFICE WORKER IN MUSASHINO

499
00:35:48,459 --> 00:35:50,169
Packing up more things?

500
00:36:00,930 --> 00:36:02,056
I myself

501
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:04,517
don't even know

502
00:36:05,601 --> 00:36:07,478
what I'm trying to do.

503
00:36:11,148 --> 00:36:12,566
But I…

504
00:36:13,484 --> 00:36:15,736
don't want the MEJ to just disappear.

505
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:22,827
I might be the only one

506
00:36:24,036 --> 00:36:25,621
who still has lingering regrets.

507
00:36:28,249 --> 00:36:30,376
It might be pointless in itself

508
00:36:32,044 --> 00:36:34,130
to worry so much.

509
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:38,926
But…

510
00:36:40,761 --> 00:36:42,596
I just don't want to let it end here.

511
00:36:49,145 --> 00:36:53,941
Please let me help with the investigation
of the Shiramine case too.

512
00:37:09,915 --> 00:37:11,250
Please do,

513
00:37:12,251 --> 00:37:13,336
Ms. Kiryu.

514
00:37:25,931 --> 00:37:27,933
I handed out flyers again yesterday,

515
00:37:28,017 --> 00:37:30,353
and a lot of people accepted them.

516
00:37:31,729 --> 00:37:34,440
Everyone is taking action
for you, Shinichi.

517
00:37:36,942 --> 00:37:38,069
Shinichi?

518
00:37:40,112 --> 00:37:41,155
Fifteen years…

519
00:37:43,366 --> 00:37:44,658
have passed.

520
00:37:51,123 --> 00:37:53,626
The next one to be executed might be me.

521
00:37:55,211 --> 00:37:57,421
I will never let that happen.
I'm going to--

522
00:37:57,505 --> 00:37:59,256
You won't make it in time.

523
00:38:35,668 --> 00:38:37,253
Who might you be?

524
00:38:39,463 --> 00:38:41,090
I'm sorry for the sudden visit.

525
00:38:41,882 --> 00:38:42,925
I am Kiryu,

526
00:38:43,551 --> 00:38:47,346
the supervisor of Medical Examiner Japan.

527
00:38:47,430 --> 00:38:50,057
Could you please spare me
some time to talk?

528
00:38:55,521 --> 00:38:57,481
You've come all the way to my house.

529
00:38:57,565 --> 00:38:59,150
What are you planning?

530
00:39:02,153 --> 00:39:03,571
I am terribly sorry.

531
00:39:06,031 --> 00:39:09,618
But there is something
I want you to look at.

532
00:39:19,753 --> 00:39:20,754
What is this?

533
00:39:22,715 --> 00:39:24,633
These are the autopsy reports

534
00:39:24,717 --> 00:39:27,553
of all the bodies that Dr. Masumi
has dissected at MEJ.

535
00:39:28,804 --> 00:39:30,306
Why would you show me?

536
00:39:30,389 --> 00:39:32,641
I brought them on my own judgment.

537
00:39:34,435 --> 00:39:37,396
I wanted you to read them.

538
00:39:43,986 --> 00:39:48,574
Since MEJ was closed down
after just a few months,

539
00:39:49,450 --> 00:39:54,038
we didn't get to handle that many bodies.

540
00:39:54,830 --> 00:39:55,998
Still,

541
00:39:57,208 --> 00:40:03,464
Dr. Masumi has faced the life of each
and every deceased person earnestly.

542
00:40:05,132 --> 00:40:06,592
Thanks to that,

543
00:40:06,675 --> 00:40:09,929
the truth that had been overlooked
was brought to light.

544
00:40:11,889 --> 00:40:13,807
We were able to save the living,

545
00:40:14,725 --> 00:40:17,478
and also deliver the voices
of the deceased.

546
00:40:21,190 --> 00:40:22,775
Dr. Masumi…

547
00:40:24,944 --> 00:40:29,615
never let even the slightest thing amiss
go unnoticed.

548
00:40:33,536 --> 00:40:35,704
He will always reveal the truth.

549
00:40:37,581 --> 00:40:38,749
Because

550
00:40:40,042 --> 00:40:41,919
he does it for the sake of the deceased,

551
00:40:44,463 --> 00:40:47,174
but also for the sake of those
who are alive.

552
00:41:04,608 --> 00:41:05,818
Welcome back.

553
00:41:06,402 --> 00:41:07,236
Thank you.

554
00:41:20,541 --> 00:41:24,837
I'm very sorry for making
a one-sided request the other day

555
00:41:25,337 --> 00:41:29,633
without considering your feelings.

556
00:41:35,639 --> 00:41:36,724
After you left,

557
00:41:37,975 --> 00:41:40,352
I thought about what you told me.

558
00:41:44,148 --> 00:41:46,066
In order to get a retrial,

559
00:41:46,567 --> 00:41:48,611
we need to find new evidence,

560
00:41:49,278 --> 00:41:55,159
or otherwise prove that the evidence used
for the verdict was flawed.

561
00:41:58,912 --> 00:42:00,414
We have been searching

562
00:42:01,290 --> 00:42:05,127
for a forensic medicine doctor
who would redo the evaluation.

563
00:42:06,754 --> 00:42:07,588
However,

564
00:42:08,589 --> 00:42:10,716
no one would take the job.

565
00:42:11,759 --> 00:42:12,718
No one?

566
00:42:13,385 --> 00:42:19,933
A re-evaluation is also an act of refuting
Professor Kujo's results.

567
00:42:20,851 --> 00:42:24,396
Since he was an authority
in the forensic medicine world…

568
00:42:25,773 --> 00:42:30,277
I think everyone had their hesitations
about taking it on.

569
00:42:32,363 --> 00:42:36,283
As well as that, demanding a retrial

570
00:42:36,909 --> 00:42:41,455
means objecting to the past judgment
of the prosecution.

571
00:42:43,123 --> 00:42:46,001
There wasn't a single doctor
who would go out of their way

572
00:42:46,085 --> 00:42:49,296
to take a request that would turn
the prosecution into an enemy.

573
00:42:59,139 --> 00:43:01,433
RESULTS OF INVESTIGATION

574
00:43:01,517 --> 00:43:03,644
These are the prosecution's materials

575
00:43:04,436 --> 00:43:07,106
which we obtained
through evidence disclosure.

576
00:43:12,027 --> 00:43:13,278
Mr. Mizusawa…

577
00:43:16,490 --> 00:43:17,783
I still

578
00:43:18,742 --> 00:43:20,661
cannot forgive you.

579
00:43:24,832 --> 00:43:27,292
But I will entrust you with this.

580
00:43:31,755 --> 00:43:34,925
Please prove that the autopsy results

581
00:43:36,051 --> 00:43:37,803
were fabricated.

582
00:43:45,102 --> 00:43:46,186
I promise

583
00:43:47,688 --> 00:43:49,898
I will reveal the truth.

584
00:44:07,624 --> 00:44:10,961
Subtitle translation by: Maslin F.

